section.section:
The authorizing resolution shall:
Cite the authority for the issuance of the notes and the amount authorized; and
Fix:
The maturity or maturities;
The interest rate or rates or manner of determining the rate or rates, which may include a variable rate;
Other terms on the notes;
The price or prices at which the notes will be sold, which may be at, above, or below the face value of the notes or the manner of determining the price or prices at which the notes will be sold;
The manner of the sale of the notes, which may be by private negotiation by the county with a prospective purchaser or purchasers, if deemed by the county to be for the county's best interest; and
The terms or conditions, if any, under which notes may or shall be redeemed prior to their stated maturity.
